{
  "stem": "26111.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When I then started high school-- which was early, before the-- before high school is usually started-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] it was about age eight, nine, I, I suppose, must have been.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there, I remember it much more clearly because there, it was on an adult note there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The, the, the, the last year at elementary school was the final year of childhood, in that sense.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "First year of high school was the first year of adolescence, the first experience of adolescence.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Even though I was only nine, I was surrounded by boys that ranged typically from 10 to 18.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so-- and I was treated far more as an adult, insulted more as an adult.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was quite a dividing line between the tone in elementary school and at high school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the high school, I had two friends.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One was a full Jew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The other was a half-Jew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the-- they were both friends, no more.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They weren't close friends.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The chap whose-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] whom I call a half-Jew, i.e., his, his father-- his name was Blum, B-L-U-M.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I think his name was Gerdt.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But anyway, he was a provincial ice-skating champion.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He was a very good athlete, and-- already starting as a child.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he could have, if he wanted-- he was kind of wooed by the other boys and-- in the sense that he could have declared himself to be with them and jeered at the Jews, or he could have done what he did, which was to declare-- to get beaten up rather than do the beating up, which-- and we were side by side.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were both-- I was not an athletic champion.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But, but I was more physical.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Poor [?",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
